        label: 'Andrew Eustace',
        content:
          '<p><strong>Rev <a href="../person/33716">Andrew Eustace </a></strong>(1833-1893) was born in Dublin and educated at Castleknock College and St Patrick\'s College, Maynooth where he matriculated into Logic in 1849. In October 1854, Eustace went to America where he studied at Carondolet Seminary in St. Louis, Missouri. Rev <a href="../person/34238">P<strong>atrick Feehan</strong>,</a>later Archbishop of Chicago and with whom Eustace had studied with at Maynooth, was then president of Carondolet Seminary. Serving in Chicago and St Louis, Eustace died a week before his 60th birthday in 1893. He was a cousin of Archbishop <strong><a href="../person/38619">Peter Kenrick</a></strong>  of St Louis, Missouri, who also studied at St Patrick’s College, Maynooth. </p>',
