        label: 'Bishop Thomas Hussey',
        content:
          '<p>Thomas Hussey (1741-1803): first president of the ‘Royal Catholic College of St Patrick’; key figure in the Irish Catholic Enlightenment; priest of Meath diocese, educated in Seville, later chaplain to the Spanish Embassy in London, rebuilt the embassy chapel. Politically active for the easing of penal laws, he knew Edmund Burke; appointed president in 1795, bishop of Waterford; a dispute over the provision of Catholic chaplains in the British army cost him government support. He died in a drowning accident.  </p>',
