        updatedBy: '531',
        label: 'Classpieces help',
        content:
          '<p>The Classpieces page is made up of two columns, the <strong>Filters</strong> column on the left and the <strong>Classpieces</strong> column on the right.</p>\n<h4>Filters</h4>\n<p>The <strong>Filters</strong> column allows the visitor to filter the list of items shown in the <strong>Classpieces</strong> column. The available filters are: </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Event types</li>\n<li>Organisations</li>\n<li>Dates</li>\n</ol>\n<h5>Event types</h5>\n<p>The <strong>Event types</strong> filter allows the visitor to filter by an associated event type. When a visitor selects one or more event type filters the classpieces list will only display classpieces that are associated with the events of that type.</p>\n<h5>Organisations</h5>\n<p>The <strong>Organisations</strong> filter allows the visitor to filter by one or more associated organisations. When a visitor selects one or more organisations the classpieces list will only display classpieces that are associated with these organisations. There is an additional dropdown list that filters organisations by their respective type to allow the visitor to locate the desired organisations more easily.</p>\n<h5>Dates</h5>\n<p>The <strong>Dates</strong> filter allows the visitor to filter by dates. First the visitor must select the type of the date match from a drop down list. The date match type may be one of the following: </p>\n<ol>\n<li>Exact</li>\n<li>Before</li>\n<li>After</li>\n<li>In Range</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If the visitor selects one of the three first types she/he then must set the date. A datepicker is available to help select the proper date more easily and ensure that the date is supplied in the correct format (dd/mm/yyyy). If the visitor selects the last option, In Range one input appears to allow the visitor to input the appropriate end date.<br />The visitor must trigger the filter by clicking the submit button.</p>\n<h5>General remarks</h5>\n<p>The filters work in combination. Each time a visitor selects a filter the filters themselves are also filtered and only the values that may be applied to the available subset of classpieces remain visible, thus enabling further filtering the results.</p>\n<p>Every search filter has a small <em><strong>clear </strong></em>button. This button clears only the selected values of that specific filter. There is also a generic <em><strong>clear all </strong></em>button next to the <strong>Filters</strong> heading that clears all the selected filters. </p>\n<p>When a visitor sets filters the filter values are stored in the memory. When the visitor navigates back to the classpieces webpage the filters are still active. This memory is reset when the visitor refreshes the webpage or opens it in a new window/tab.</p>\n<h4>Classpieces</h4>\n<p>The classpieces column contains the following:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>the number of total items</li>\n<li>the search bar</li>\n<li>the limit dropdown list</li>\n<li>the pagination</li>\n<li>the list of classpieces</li>\n</ol>\n<h5>Number of total items</h5>\n<p>This number is updated when the visitor sets filters and/or performs a search to reflect the total number of matches.</p>\n<h5>Search bar</h5>\n<p>The search bar visibility may be toggled by clicking the lens icon next to the number of total items. The search bar has a generic search input where the visitor may enter a search term. This term is matched against the labels of the classpieces and the results are returned. To submit the search the visitor may either press the enter key or click on the search button next to the search input. The search input contains a round x button that works as a clear search button, when a visitor clicks this button the search term is removed and the system returns all the classpieces.</p>\n<h5>Limit</h5>\n<p>The Limit dropdown is where the visitor sets the number of items she/he wishes to view per page.</p>\n<h5>Pagination</h5>\n<p>The pagination allows the visitor to navigate through the available pages of classpieces. The visitor may navigate to the first/last page, next/previous page or to a page number. The user may also input a page number directly, a feature that may prove useful when there is a very big number of pages.</p>\n<h5>List of classpieces</h5>\n<p>The list of classpieces contains a list of the available classpieces per page. This list changes according to the filters set by the visitor and the search term. Each item in the list contains the thumbnail of a classpiece and the label of the classpiece.</p>',
