        updatedBy: '53930',
        label: 'Heatmap help',
        content:
          "<p>The Heatmap visualisation is a graphical representation of the distribution of people contained within the Clericus database that are associated with a diocese. The heatmap shows hotspots depending on the number of people associated with a location. The color of each hotspot on the map indicates the population density for that location as shown in more detail in the legend at the bottom right corner of the heatmap.</p>\n<p>Depending on the zoom level of the map some numbers may appear on the map. This indicates a cluster of locations. When the visitor's mouse is over one of these numbers a polygon appears with each location being represented by the appropriate polygon corner.</p>\n<p>While zooming in marker pins appear representing an individual location. Clicking on a marker pin will open a small popup with the locations details, i.e. the name of the associated diocese and it's associated people.</p>\n<p>The visitor can click on the search icon to open up the search panel. There the visitor is presented with the list of all available items. Entering a search term will filter the available items. When the visitor clicks on one of the items the map will focus on that item.</p>",
