        updatedBy: '532',
        label: 'Images from the Irish College Paris',
        content:
          '<p>The Irish Cultural Centre Paris has kindly supplied the Clericus project with several images for display on the website\'s homepage.</p>\n<p>The building of the Collège des Irlandais, or Irish College, in Paris was formerly home to a large collegiate community of Irish priests, seminarians and lay scholars whose origins stretch back to 1578. It was completely restored at the beginning of the 21st century to inaugurate the Centre Culturel Irlandais, Ireland’s cultural headquarters on the European continent. Over 2,000 biographical entries relating to ICP students, covering the period c.1825 to c.1939, can be accessed via the Clericus database. For more information on the Irish College and its successor, the Irish Cultural Centre, see <a href="https://www.centreculturelirlandais.com/content/files/History-CCI-English.pdf">here</a>.</p>',
